content:
Basically, Katekyo Hitman Reborn is one of the best animes I've ever seen and it has the most original storyline in my opinion. I've rewatched the anime over 6 times from the first episode right on to the final 203 and I just can't help to feel like watching it again! 
It's not everyday you see an anime starting off with a little baby mafioso coming to the doorsteps with an adorable shapeshifting chameleon or a mafia that compiles members from the age 13 (5?!) to 16 and uses rings and box weapons than just guys in black carrying guns in fancy shiny black cars.I enjoyed KHR more than I enjoyed other animes that have gone over a hundred episodes (Naruto, Bleach etc...). 


Now, let's cut down the parts bit by bit aye?


Story;

I've seen many comments, reviews and discussions about KHR and basically, everyone is talking about the downfall of KHR which was the first 20 episodes. Yeah, I actually dropped the anime after watching 2 episodes but I couldn't help to feel that there was something much more afterwards so I persevered and continued watching and I found the 20 episodes HILARIOUS! It's hard not to laugh when a little baby assasin dressed up in a cow suit come jumping around with pink grenades and stuffs in a bazooka, rocket launcher and tons of candies in his afro. (Lambo FTW!) After 20 episodes, the story begins loosening the comedy and the actual seriousness begins. From here, I asure you, you won't be able to stop watching. The transitioning from a simple comedy to a serious action is still filled with a few funny scenes but you can see the development and it will hook you up.

9/10 for me!


Art;

Yeah..yeah... For most art-obsessed anime viewers, KHR may not have the best art and the characters may look weird at some angle or so but I don't think this is a problem to keep you from watching it. During the Future Arc and all, I actually find the characters all quite decent and after rewatching it a few times, KHR has quite the number of hot guys from looks to personality. The action scenes are very nicely done and I find it 8/10 in my taste.


Sound;

Don't let me BEGIN with the soundtrack...it is EPIC! I love all of the opening songs and the character songs! The second opening really got the feel of the Varia Arc and it also shows the great development of the characters since the arc houses the time where most of the characters go through a change in ability. I have nothing to complain about here so it's an all 10/10!


Character;

This is probably the main strong point of the entire anime. The characters are all amazing in their own way! Let's see...Tsuna first started out as a whiny no-good kid whose fate is turned and twisted to become a big mafia boss only at the age of 14. I guess, Tsuna's development is the main thing in KHR and I absolutely love how he journeys through the story and when I reached episode 203, I realised on how Tsuna had changed so much but still has the same normal aura around him. This doesn't change with the other characters. They went through a lot but they still had their own orginal personality strong and his gives out a concrete character. They changed, heck yeah, but they're still who they were right in the beginning; Hibari being the bloodthirsty kinky character I love so much, Lambo being as annoying as ever, Yamamoto being as easy-going he could be and Ryohei going all to the extreme!!! x'DD I love all of the characters...except for a few but I've got nothing to hate about them... 10/10 to the EXTREMEE!!!!!


Enjoyment;

do I NEED to elaborate on this? Well, I can't give it a 10/10 since there were flaws but I can live with them. I enjoyed it enough to rewatch it fully for 6 times and I'm still up for another round! What more can I say about this? 


Overall;

a total MASTERPIECE. I'm currently catching up on the manga which is just twice as awesome with the new arc and all. =3


NOW GO AND WATCH KATEKYO HITMAN REBORN! The storyline is epic and the characters are to die for! (Hibari =
